## 🚀 Installation

```bash
git clone https://github.com/f1smv/spot-watcher-dx.git
cd spot-watcher-dx
chmod +x start.sh
./start.sh
```

The application will be available at `http://localhost:8000`

---

## ⚙️ Technical Architecture

- Backend: Python / Flask
- Frontend: HTML / CSS / JavaScript
- Cluster: Telnet DX Cluster
- Analysis: dedicated Python scripts
- Storage: memory + local JSON files + **SQLite** (v10.0)

No cloud dependency.

---

## 🗂️ Version History

### v10.0 — Predictive Engine · Sparklines · Push Alerts (optional)

#### 🔮 Personal Predictive Engine (`predictor.py`)

A new personal intelligence layer: the application learns from your activity and anticipates the openings that matter to you.

**Layer 1 — SQLite collection** (`data/predictor.sqlite`)
- `spot_log` table: every received spot is recorded (call, DXCC, band, mode, SPD score, timestamp)
- `es_events` table: every 6m spot generates a sporadic-E event (month, UTC hour, direction prefix)
- `sessions` table: operator sessions tracked via browser heartbeat
- `missing_dxcc` table: missing DXCCs synchronized from the LoTW cache
- Automatic purge of data older than 90 days

**Layer 2 — Probabilistic scoring**
- Seasonal/hourly Es patterns: base probabilities by month × UTC hour (peak May–July, 07z–18z)
- Directional boost: some Es paths are historically more frequent (EU→EU strong, EU→JA moderate…)
- Band factor: 6m = SFI-independent (Es), HF = weighted by SFI and Kp
- Local history bonus: recorded events reinforce the score for the same time slots
- Missing DXCC cross-reference: only openings toward entities still needed are surfaced

**Layer 3 — Predictions displayed in COCKPIT mode**
- New **🔮 PERSONAL PREDICTIONS** panel in COCKPIT column 1
- TOP 5 most probable windows over the next 24 hours
- Each prediction: UTC time, band, target DXCC, % score, color bar, explanatory tip
- 10-minute cache, auto-recalculated on every switch to cockpit mode
- Example: *"Strong probability (68%) of 6m opening toward JT1 between 14h–17z — JT1 missing in FT8"*

**New backend routes**
- `GET /api/predictions` — personalized predictions (cross-referenced with LoTW if active)
- `GET /api/predictor/stats` — collection stats (logged spots, Es events, sessions)
- `POST /api/presence` — operator heartbeat (suppresses push alerts while you're on the page)

#### 📊 Sparklines in the DX Feed

Next to each callsign in the COCKPIT **DX Spot Feed**:
- Inline 40×14 px canvas, **6 bars of 10 minutes** covering the last hour
- At a glance: *"just arrived"* vs *"calling for 40 minutes"*
- Cyan intensity proportional to spot count in each time bucket
- Data from `/api/spot_history` — no additional collection, existing RAM history reused
- Auto-injected by MutationObserver: always up to date without page reload

#### 🔔 Smart push alerts (optional — disabled by default)

Alert infrastructure available, disabled until `NTFY_URL` is configured.

**3 alert types:**
1. **Watchlist spotted** — a tracked call appears on the cluster
2. **NEW DXCC** — a missing LoTW entity is active on a needed band
3. **6m opening** — surge detected (> N spots / 10 min)

**Built-in anti-spam:**
- 15-minute cooldown per call/type stored in SQLite
- **Presence filter**: if you're on the page (heartbeat < 45s), no alert is sent

**PUSH badge** in the DX Feed title — shows status (active / inactive), click for details.

**ntfy.sh configuration (if desired):**
```bash
# Create a topic on ntfy.sh (free, no account required)
export NTFY_URL="https://ntfy.sh/neuraldx-f1smv-XXXXXX"

# On your phone: install the ntfy.sh app, subscribe to the same topic
# Test from the app:
curl -s -X POST http://localhost:8000/api/ntfy/test
```

Self-hosting on the Pi is possible (single Go binary, ~20 MB RAM).

**New routes:**
- `GET /api/ntfy/status` — status, cooldowns, recent alerts
- `POST /api/ntfy/test` — send a test notification

#### 🎨 Unified design system (v9.6 → integrated v10.0)

The COCKPIT visual language is now **the design of the entire application**:
- HUD background with 32px grid and CRT scanlines as fixed layers
- Glassmorphism on all CLASSIC and SMART panels (`backdrop-filter: blur(18px)`)
- `.panel-header` titles styled as ck-title with glowing dot and cyan gradient band
- Mode buttons with distinct glow states (cyan / purple / orange)
- Header: frosted glass + title glow, translucent ticker
- Tables: cyan-glow headers, hover rows
- Scrollbars: cyan→orange gradient
- Structural fix: `#header-row2` was rendered outside `#header` since v9.x

#### 🔧 HF Propagation panel corrected

The COCKPIT **HF PROPAGATION** panel was displaying incorrect VHF/UHF data:
- Corrected bands: `80m / 40m / 20m / 17m / 15m / 12m / 10m` (instead of `50MHz / 70MHz / 144MHz / 432MHz`)
- X axis: 24 columns 00z→23z (instead of 6 slots 06z→21z)
- Palette: red→green matching the classic panel
- "Now" line: white dashed line + ▼ triangle
- Inline legend: 0-20 / 20-40 / 40-60 / 60-80 / 80+
- Diurnal model: 80m/40m favored at night, 10m/12m/15m SFI-dependent

---

### v9.5 — Fine Geolocation + Gaussian Heatmap + Direct Spot Send

**Fine geolocation of spots (Option A+B)**

- `CALLSIGN_ZONES` table: 100+ precise call districts (USA W0-W9/K/N by zone digit, Canada VE1-7, Japan JA0-9, Russia UA0-9, Australia VK1-7, Germany DL1-9, Spain EA1-8, France, Italy)
- `_callsign_jitter()`: deterministic ±1.5° offset based on callsign MD5
- `get_precise_latlon()`: 4 levels — 3-char prefix → 2-char → US zone digit → country centroid + jitter
- Fixes the bug where all USA spots appeared at the same point (37.6, -91.87)

**6m Gaussian Heatmap (Magic Band cockpit)**

- Replaces distance-colored circles with a **continuous heat layer** (weather radar style)
- Each spot emits a ~600km Gaussian (adaptive radius via Leaflet projection)
- Relative normalization by measured max — densest zone is always red
- Gamma 0.65 correction, palette: blue → cyan → green → yellow → orange → red
- Auto-redraws on pan/zoom and Leaflet `load` event

**Direct spot send on click**

- Click any row in HF/VHF table → spot sent immediately via `POST /api/spot`
- Confirmation toast bottom-right (green ✅ or red ❌)

**FT8 DXpedition frequencies**

- Added 14090 kHz (20m) and 18095 kHz (17m) as FT8 frequencies

**Watchlist Purge v2**

- New `data/wl_activity.json` — persists `{last_spot, end_date, added}` per call
- Purge modal: red pre-checked rows (ended expeditions), end date in orange

> v9.3 was an unpublished work-in-progress version.

### v9.4 — WSJT-X Integration + 6m Clustering + fixes

**WSJT-X UDP Integration**

- Real-time WSJT-X UDP stream reception (port 2237)
- Full Qt binary protocol parser: Heartbeat, Status, Decode, QSOLog
- Maidenhead locator extraction from FT8 messages for precise positioning
- 30s deduplication, orange `WSJT` badge + SNR in all tables
- Compatible with Log4OM

**6m Geographic Clustering**

- 400km radius geo clustering, 5 color levels, proportional Leaflet zone halos

### v9.2 — Unified Cockpit Theme

- **Cockpit** theme becomes the application-wide default
- Inputs, buttons, tables, scrollbars harmonized across all modes

### v9.0 — NEURAL DX & COCKPIT 6 m mode

